The young bartender nods sympathetically “I know how you feel. My Aunt has been roping me into volunteering here for a few years now.” He finishes pouring your drink and says “You know if you need a moment to yourself - go check out the Trophy Room; it has years of junk they’ve collected or you could try the Back Patio - it's usually pretty quiet. You thank him, collect your drink and decide to take him up on his advice of seeking a temporary refuge.
